      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THEHORSEMAN (2) went to Saturday grade last time out and was just outclassed, though the form out of that race has worked out well. Riordan's claim comes in handy and he is a winner at this track and trip previously. Here off a freshen and can make a statement. GOLD VANCOUVER (5) is another coming here on the fresh side and will be fitter for a recent trial at Belmont. She's joined the Hayley stable since her last start in Saturday grade and she boasts a strong fresh record. Can play a leading role on her return to racing. GOLD KEEPER (4) has been narrowly beaten in his past three outings, leading them up last time out before being claimed by 1.1L close to home. Turner remains in the saddle and back in trip may hold the key today. Never missed the placings at 1100m and can make his presence felt. LUCKEE FLORAN (6) was too good over this track and trip last time out and can be tough to catch once again. PRINCE RAGNAR (1) was too good at Dongara and can repeat the dose.",
